 <H1>Policies: Object-Centric</H1> 
 <P><UL></P>

<P><LI><H2>Placing trust in objects (or keys)
</H2></P>

<P></UL><UL></P>

<P><LI><H2>Typically, protect resources with keys
</H2></P>

<P><UL></P>

<P><LI>Hand out the combination to a vault
<LI>Secret-sharing can require multiple cooperating keyholders (e.g. a safe-deposit box) 
</UL></UL><UL></P>

<P><LI><H2>Optionally compartmentalize access
</H2></P>

<P><UL></P>

<P><LI>Different interfaces have different keys
<LI>Deposit and Withdraw handles in MS COM-speak
<UL></P>

<P><LI>Possession of the right pointer limits the visible functions
<LI>
<LI>Useful when there are fewer objects than users or actions</UL></UL></UL></P>

